blocks.name: df-bigo
blocks.content: Define the function "big-O", mapping a real function g to the set of real functions "of order g(x)". Definition in section 1.1 of [AhoHopUll] p. 2. This is a generalization of "big-O of one", see ~ df-o1 and ~ df-lo1 . As explained in the comment of df-o1 , any big-O can be represented in terms of ` O(1) ` and division, see ~ elbigolo1 . (Contributed by AV, 15-May-2020.)
